HEADWORD: Digne
<hw>Digne</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>dignus</ets>. See <er>Design</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Worthy;
honorable; deserving.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Suitable; adequate; fit.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Haughty; disdainful.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dignification</ent>⟦br⟧
